The paper is about a deep learning pipeline for image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The pipeline also involves training and validation of the deep learning models, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Dixon MRI scans suggests that the paper may also be relevant to medical imaging (cs.MM). The pipeline is designed to be fast and efficient, which could be of interest to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper involves analysis of a large cohort study, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
